      "lesson title": "AI in Scriptwriting and Story Development",
      "order": 1,
      "Description": "This lesson explores how artificial intelligence tools are increasingly being used to support scriptwriting and story development, from generating dialogue to structuring plotlines. As a beginner, you will gain a clear understanding of the practical benefits these tools can offer, alongside the important risks they introduce around originality, bias, and narrative integrity. We will look at how over-reliance on AI can lead to homogenised storytelling, unintentional bias in character representation, and questions around creative ownership. By the end of this lesson, you will feel confident identifying where AI can genuinely assist your creative process and where human judgement remains essential. The goal is to help you work with these tools thoughtfully and responsibly, keeping your own voice and vision at the centre of your work.",
